quran[12]{c,v,t,f}:
  19,65,"Lord of the heavens and the earth and whatever is between them, so worship Him and persevere in worshiping Him. Do you know of anyone similar to Him?"
  19,66,"And man says, “Can it be that when{1}I am dead,I willbe brought out alive?”",footnotes:1:Qira’at: Ibn Zekwan, in one of his narrations, read it as: “…says, ‘When I am dead, will I be brought out alive?’”
  19,67,"Does man not remember that We created him earlier when he was nothing?"
  19,68,"By your<sup>sg </sup>Lord, We will surely herd them and the devils, then We will surely bring them around Hell on their knees."
  19,69,"Then out of every sect We will surely snatch those most defiant to the All-Merciful."
  19,70,"Then<i>(they will realize that) </i>We surely know better of those who are most deserving to roast in it."
  19,71,"But every single one of you is bound to approach it; this has been an unavoidable decree of your Lord."
  19,72,"Then We{1}deliver{2}those who were mindful<i>(of God) </i>and leave the unjust in it on their knees.",footnotes:1:[A grammatical shift from 3<sup><small>rd</small></sup> person to 1<sup><small>st</small></sup> person.],footnotes:2:[Qira’at: Al-Kesa’i and Ya’qub read it as: “Then We save those who…”]
  19,73,"And when Our signs{1}are read to them, evident, those who have denied say to those who have attained faith, “Which of the two groups is better in position{2}and fairerin company?”",footnotes:1:[The Arabic word used is <i>ayat</i> (singular <i>ayah</i>). <i>Ayah</i> means ‘sign’ or ‘proof’. It is also used to denote the unit of text in the Qur’an, like ‘verse’ in poetry or ‘sentence’ in prose. Each such unit is considered a ‘sign’ from God.],footnotes:2:[Qira’at: Ibn Kathir read it as: “‘Which of the two groups has a better dwelling place and is fairer in company?’”]
  19,74,"And how many a generation have We annihilated before them who surpassed them in riches and splendor?"
  19,75,"Say<sup>sg </sup>, “Whoever has been in utter misguidance, may the All-Merciful fully extend for him{1}.” Until, when they see what they were promised—either punishment or the Hour—then they will know who was in a worse position and weaker as an army.",footnotes:1:In wealth and time.
  19,76,"And Allah increases in guidance those who seek guidance. And abiding deeds of righteousness are more rewardable by your Lord and better in return."
